Cape Town - Six suspects are due to appear in the Mitchells Plain Magistrate's Court on drug-related charges after they were arrested in the sprawling Cape Town suburb. Three men and three women were found in possession of crystal methamphetamine (tik) during a raid by police after a tipoff from the community of Lentegeur, Mitchell's Plain. "Partnership policing contributed to the arrest of six suspects this afternoon in Lentegeur after they were found in possession of a large quantity of tik," police spokesperson Andrè Traut said. "Members of Lentegeur police reacted on a tipoff from the community and conducted a search operation at a residence in Pasteur Hof where three males and three females aged between 16 and 19 were arrested in possession of tik with an estimated street value of R60 000. "Once charged, they are due to make a court appearance in Mitchells Plain on a charge of dealing in drugs," Traut said.  argusnews@inl.co.za  Cape Argus